Prep and roast the potatoes: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Cut the @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch wedges. Mince the @Chives{¼%ounce}. Zest and halve the @Lemon{1}. Toss the potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Place in the oven for ~{25-30%minutes}, tossing halfway through cooking, until golden brown.

Place the @Panko Breadcrumbs{½%cup} in a #shallow dish{} with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. In a #medium bowl{}, combine the lemon zest, @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, 2 tablespoons @Sour Cream{2%ounce}, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Prep the chicken: Place the @Chicken Breasts{12%ounce} between two pieces of #plastic wrap{} and pound with a #rolling pin{}, #mallet{}, or a #heavy-bottomed pan{} until ½-inch thick. Season with salt and pepper, then toss each breast with the sour cream mixture to coat. Press the chicken into the panko mixture to adhere on both sides.

Cook the chicken: Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Working in batches, if necessary, add the chicken to the pan and cook ~{3-4%minutes} per side, until golden brown and cooked through.

> If you need to work in batches, you can reheat the cooked chicken in the oven before serving.

Make the dressing: In a #small bowl{}, whisk together 1 tablespoon @Sour Cream{2%ounce}, 1 tablespoon chives, a squeeze of lemon (about 2 teaspoons) and a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{4%teaspoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

Plate: Toss the @Arugula{2%ounce} with just enough dressing to coat and serve alongside the chicken Milanese and crispy potatoes. Sprinkle with the remaining chives and enjoy!